<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2><a>Eargo hearing aid pricing</a></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><a href="https://www.healthline.com/health/best-hearing-aid">Hearing aids are an investment</a>. While Eargo hearing aids aren’t inexpensive, they’re about half the price of some other hearing aids on the market. Eargo prices range from $1,450 to $2,950.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Eargo does have a 10 percent discount on certain models for military personnel, veterans, teachers, nurses, doctors, or first responders.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>These hearing aids are available directly from Eargo by phone or online, or via&nbsp;<a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.amazon.com/stores/Eargo/page/D0827791-C5C6-4BE9-8C96-3BDD26409E7D?&amp;linkCode=ll2&amp;tag=eargo-review-20&amp;linkId=f188aaf752fa8647c48871168d3eedc5&amp;language=en_US&amp;ref_=as_li_ss_tl&amp;ascsubtag=2a143d5c-c55c-4e91-b721-eddff61395a9&amp;correlationId=2a143d5c-c55c-4e91-b721-eddff61395a9">Amazon</a>. They’re also sold at a very small number of stores.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Monthly financing plans are available from Eargo, starting at $67 per month.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Eargo’s Max and Neo HiFi have a 1-year warranty, while the two newer models are covered for 2 years. The warranty covers unlimited repairs and one-time loss or damage per hearing aid.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://activation.healthline.com/api/member-offers/4540/redirect?lp=328&amp;amp;tc=120226&amp;amp;subid2=%2Fhealth%2Feargo-review&amp;amp;subid=eargo_leadform_universal_textlink_5001&amp;correlationId=2935decb-c674-4ec1-82e8-6b311cb22b62">UNDEFINEDEARGO</a></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2><a>Does insurance cover Eargo hearing aids?</a></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>For federal employees with FEHB, Eargo hearing aids may be completely covered. Some other insurance providers that may have hearing aid coverage include:</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:list -->
<ul><li><a href="https://www.healthline.com/health/medicare/aetna-medicare-advantage-plans">Aetna</a></li><li>some&nbsp;<a href="https://www.healthline.com/health/medicare/does-medicare-cover-hearing-aids">Medicare Advantage plans</a></li><li><a href="https://www.geha.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Government Employees Health Association</a></li><li><a href="https://www.fepblue.org/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Federal Employee Program Blue Cross</a></li></ul>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Eargo advises that you check with your insurance company before making a purchase.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2><a>Eargo return policy</a></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>You can return your Eargo hearing aids within 45 days for a full refund, but note that a couple of phone calls will probably be involved.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Learn more about Eargo’s return policies from their&nbsp;<a href="https://help.eargo.com/en/articles/4144617-45-day-right-to-return" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">help center</a>.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Return policies of retailers who sell Eargo hearing aids may differ. Check the store’s policy.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2><a>Eargo customer reviews</a></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Eargo customer reviews are mostly very positive. Customers report that they hear much better and that the devices are comfortable, easy to use, and virtually invisible. Reviewers also give high marks for the service, including the technical support.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Customers also note that Eargo hearing aids were comfortable while wearing glasses and a face mask.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Complaints vary. Some people find the Eargo hearing aids to be uncomfortable. Some say they malfunctioned quickly, and others had difficulty getting a refund or reaching customer service.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Eargo replied to complaints made on some websites, such as ConsumerAffairs, and offered solutions.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>On&nbsp;<a href="https://www.consumeraffairs.com/health/eargo-inc.html" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Consumer Affairs</a>, Eargo has a rating of 4.3 out of 5 stars.&nbsp;<a href="https://www.retirementliving.com/reviews/eargo-hearing-aids" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Retirement Living</a>&nbsp;gives it an overall rating of nearly 5 stars.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.eargo.com/reviews?correlationId=0934b773-577e-4ab0-9b7b-9d17dc962de6">Eargo’s website</a>&nbsp;has more reviews than other sites, with an average of about 4.5 stars.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The company is not rated by the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.bbb.org/us/ca/san-jose/profile/hearing-assistive-devices/eargo-inc-1216-415118" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Better Business Bureau</a>.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2><a>How to get started</a></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Eargo’s website is a good place to start to get an overview of the hearing aids and how they work. The website has many short videos with details about the use and maintenance of the hearing aid.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Eargo offers a free hearing check and evaluation of your lifestyle to help determine if Eargo will work for you.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>You can ask for a sample device to see how the Eargo models fit in your ear. The sample device isn’t a working model.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>You can call Eargo to ask questions. The company also offers an online Zoom hearing auditory screening with a trained professional to help you select the best product for you.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Eargo offers this consulting service with an auditory professional free for the lifetime of your hearing aids.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2><a>Eargo vs. competitors</a></h2>
