<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2><a>Frequently asked questions</a></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3>Is Eargo a new brand?</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The Eargo brand has been around since 2010 and was founded by French ear, nose, and throat surgeon Dr. Florent Michel and his son Raphael Michel.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>However, it wasn’t until 2015 that Eargo launched its first hearing aids. They introduced the Eargo Max in 2018, the Neo HiFi in 2020, Eargo 5 in 2021, and Eargo 6 in 2022.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3>Does Eargo offer a free sample trial period?</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Eargo does not offer a free trial period, but they do offer a 45-day right to return period that starts when your hearing aids are delivered.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>To help you get the most from your Eargo hearing aids, the company provides a scheduled call with licensed personal hearing professionals (PHPs) who act as your hearing coach during your right to return period.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>There are also helpful videos and client care specialists to make sure you have a positive experience.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Eargo also offers a&nbsp;<a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.eargo.com/sample-kit?correlationId=611cb108-277a-497e-9088-6327fe0938be">free fit and feel sample</a>, which is a nonworking model. You can use it to test the fit and comfort of the design.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3>Should I use Eargo if I don’t have severe hearing loss?</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>According to Eargo, they have designed their hearing aids to help mainly with mild to moderate high-frequency hearing loss. These problems are usually due to typical wear and tear from noise and aging.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>If you’re unsure if Eargo can help you, you can use the&nbsp;<a target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.eargo.com/hearing-check.html?correlationId=b910e7c3-b42f-4676-ab78-0411a2cb5a57">hearing screening</a>&nbsp;tool on the Eargo website to find out.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3>Is Eargo a real hearing aid?</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Yes, Eargo sells four models of hearing aids that are classified as medical devices by the FDA.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3>Is Eargo just an amplifier?</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Eargo’s devices are hearing aids, not just amplifiers. This means that Eargo hearing aids use technology to make specific sounds louder while reducing other sounds, like background noise. An amplifier, on the other hand, simply makes all sounds louder.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3>How long does Eargo last?</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Eargo offers rechargeable hearing aids that have about 16 hours of battery life on a full charge.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3>What does Eargo look like in the ear?</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Eargo’s hearing aid models are designed to sit inside of ear so that they’re barely visible.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2><a>The bottom line</a></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Eargo is a fast-growing company with an innovative product that they’re continuing to improve.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>If your hearing is impaired and you’ve avoided buying a hearing aid because of its cost or look, Eargo may be a good option to consider.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

